# Lambda deployment zip

When you change any file under `api/` (especially `api/index.js`), **always** create the Lambda deployment zip so the user can upload it without running the command themselves.

## Required output name

- **Always** write **`contest-api.zip`** at the **repo root** (same folder as `package.json` / `src/`).
- **Never** use other names (e.g. `api.zip`). The user and any scripts expect **`contest-api.zip`**.

## Correct contents (Lambda expects files at zip root)

The zip must contain **`index.js`**, **`bracket-regions.json`**, **`team-espn-ids.json`**, and **`node_modules/`** at the **top level** of the archive — i.e. create the zip **from inside `api/`** with those items, not a nested `api/` folder. Uploading a zip whose root is `api/index.js` can break the handler if Lambda is configured for `index.handler` at zip root.

**PowerShell** (from repo root):

```powershell
Set-Location api
Compress-Archive -Path index.js,bracket-regions.json,team-espn-ids.json,node_modules -DestinationPath ..\contest-api.zip -Force
Set-Location ..
```

Run this at the end of your response whenever you have edited API code, and tell the user **`contest-api.zip`** is ready to upload to the Lambda console.
